      "sc:citation": {
        "@id": "https://doi.org/10.18129/B9.bioc.scoreInvHap"
      },
      "sc:description": "scoreInvHap can get the samples' inversion status of known inversions. scoreInvHap uses SNP data as input and requires the following information about the inversion: genotype frequencies in the different haplotypes, R2 between the region SNPs and inversion status and heterozygote genotypes in the reference. The package include this data for 21 inversions.",
